\'a0\'a0\'a0 ----- TEXT:\
\cf4 \cb5 \'a0\'a0\'a0 The paper extends the authors\'92 previous work [12], which focuses on essential aspects of encoding the run-to-completion in Event-B, and thus added a little significant contribution. Overall, it is more like a tool experience paper than a research one.\
\'a0\'a0\'a0\
\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0Firstly, the paper is not easy to follow the contents, partly because the authors may assume that readers are familiar with the works on which the the present materials are built.\
\'a0\'a0\'a0\
\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0Secondly, the encoding method of the run-to-completion semantics, in Section 3, is clear, but seems a kind of standard practices. It is also interesting to use graphical representations similar to StateCharts. The authors may refer to their previous work [12] if it follows the contents already published.\cf3 \cb1 \
\cf2 \cb7 \'a0\'a0\'a0\
\cf2 \cb7 \'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0Here is a list of questions and comments.\
\'a0\'a0\'a0 (1) 2.1: It is not clear how triggers are de-queued. It seems to assume a FIFO queue.\cf3 \cb1 \
\cf2 \cb7 \'a0\'a0\'a0\
\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0(2) 2.2: It needs concise but detailed explanation of the Event-B refinement so that the discussions afterwards are more understandable. e.g.] refinement is defined in term of forward simulation, the event is a basic linguistic component to be refined, how the guard strengthening is\
\'a0\'a0\'a0 related to the superposition refinement, \'85\cf3 \cb1 \
\'a0\'a0\'a0\
\cf2 \cb7 \'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0(3) 4: There are several sentences referring to the method in Syriani et al. [4], but they do not provide any significant information to those not familiar with the work in [4]. All are suggested to move to the last paragraph in Section 6, which already has come summary discussion connecting to the work [4].\cf3 \cb1 \
\'a0\'a0\'a0\
\cf2 \cb7 \'a0\'a0\'a0\cf2 \cb7 \'a0(4) 5: The word \'93ProB\'94 appeared suddenly here. It must be accompanied with appropriate references.\cf9 \cb2 \
\'a0\'a0\'a0\cf3 \cb1 \
\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0(5) 5: The paper enumerates four aspects that are new to the current paper as compared with [11,12]. The explanations or rationales are not clear. Is the first aspect related to the \'93implicit consumption\'94? Does the third aspect come from the Event-B refinement?\
\'a0\'a0\'a0\
\cf2 \cb7 \'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0(6) 7: Naively, a property P is checked in stable states that are reachable according to a run-to-completion step. The paper translates P to P\'92, and is desirable to explain the reason in connection with the naive observation mentioned before.\cf3 \cb1 \
